What do we do at Kodifly? 

Founded in 2021, Kodifly is a fast-growing start-up backed by the Nvidia Inception, HKSTP’s Incubation, HKAI Lab accelerator and HKU Deeptech 100. We strive to accelerate smart city transformation with mobility and transportation A.I. including AIoT systems integration, video and LiDAR analytics solutions.




Our solutions use computer vision, deep learning and AI software to analyse images and 3D spatial data acquired from different sensors, including LiDAR and video cameras, generating actionable insight for infrastructure maintenance, safety enhancement and cost reduction for the transportation industry.




About the Job

Kodifly is looking for a highly passionate & self-motivated Junior AI Engineer to solve all problems in the field of engineering. You will get a unique opportunity to play a key role in our core A.I. product development. You are also allowed to touch on different things and implement creative ideas and work closely with our passionate team. 




What you will be Doing:

Optimize and enhance the computational efficiency of algorithms and software design;
Setup and manage our AI development and production infrastructure;
Build AI models from scratch, help product manager and key stakeholders understand the results;
Create APIs and help clients to put the results of the AI models into operations;
Keep current with the latest AI research relevant to the business domain;
Design, develop, maintain and implement A.I. applications which will be integrated or on top of web-based applications or software development kits;
Deploy AI models into production;
Improves operations by conducting systems analysis and recommending changes in policies and procedures.




Job Requirements:

Bachelor’s and/or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or related technical discipline;
Graduates in 2021 / 2022 are welcome;
Experience in Cloud computing & AWS; 
Experience in AI Model design, development, or implementation;
Proficiency in Python & JavaScript; 
Familiar with popular AI frameworks like Onnx, Cuda, Tensorflow, PyTorch, PaddlePaddle, OpenCV, etc;
Strong problem-solving skills;
Good command of written and spoken English;
Knowledge of computer vision, algorithms, and image processing;
Knowledge of professional A.I. software engineering and best practices for the full software development life cycle, including coding standards, code reviews, source control management, build processes, testing, and operations




Why Kodifly? 

Opportunities to work on state-of-the-art technologies
International, energetic and friendly team environment
Exceptional growth potential in a challenging and dynamic environment
Opportunities to take a strong sense of ownership




Benefits

Opportunity for professional development and training courses
Medical insurance
Free coffee and snacks
Regular team-building activities
12-day annual leave




